## Design Recommendations from Research

Based on survey findings and strategic insights, the following recommendations inform CareSplit’s MVP design and product strategy:
Dual Payment Modes (MVP-Critical)
Include fixed monthly auto-debit for salaried users.
Include flexible-before-due-date or open-balance model for irregular-income earners.
Both modes should launch simultaneously to cover 100% of target users.

Trust-Centric Auto-Debit Onboarding
Provide visual walkthroughs explaining how auto-debit works.
Highlight full control features: pause, skip, reschedule, and payment calendar.
Use credible branding and transparent fee disclosures to build confidence.

Default Risk Mitigation
Implement grace periods for insufficient funds.
Send 48-hour advance notifications before deductions.
Include low-balance alerts and one-tap reschedule options.
Stress Reduction & Financial Clarity
Present clear, upfront breakdowns of total bill and installment schedule.
Offer reminders and dashboards to reduce anxiety associated with medical costs.

Formalization of Informal Practices
Convert informal borrowing and manual split attempts into structured, automated plans.
Ensure platform complements insurance/HMOs rather than competing.
Education for First-Time Users
Highlight benefits of recurring payments and structured installments.
Address common concerns: fraud/security, losing control, and unexpected deductions.
